dct_title_s: The Gulf of Arta surveyed in 1830
dct_description_sm: Relief shown by hachures and spot heights. Depth shown by isobaths and soundings. Estuaries of Louros and Arachthos rivers are shown. From: The Journal of the Royal Geographical Society of London. Vol. 3 (1833), pp. 77-94; held in Firestone Library. Call number: G7 .J687 v.3 1833
dct_publisher_sm: London : published for the Journal of the Royal Geographical Society, by John Murray, Albemarle St., July 1833.
